<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>To pull ya only bloody need enough to spear or darkness em.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Speaking from experience, as a higher level Shadow Knight (62nd level) and a competent puller/tank, I never used my spear line to pull, The terror line is cheaper, and gives you more aggro points, which will be needed to keep mob off the slower and debuffer, once a shaman or a chanter drops slow and cripple, or debuffs such as malo and tash, all eyes will be on them for the mob, so for aggro sake, the Terror line is the way to go...<br>
<br>
Though once you get spells like Mental Corruption and Deathly Temptation, mana issues are not as big of a deal...<br>
<br>
But then again, not all SK's are wise in that department...<br>
