<br>
When I used to pull and tank at the same time, which was most of the time I was in a group, simply because its easier on the mana to pull and tank than it is to pull, FD then get back up after you've lost aggro, being that Death Peace is an expensive mana spell... even if you have a large mana pool.  Terror line is a cheap mana cost spell to attain a good bit of aggro points, normally when I'd pull, I'd be able to cast Terror of Death at least 3 times, which is more than enough initial aggro points  that the slower could land a slow before the mob arrived to the party.<br>
<br>
And if your running either KEI/Mental Corruption combo, or a Deathly Temptation/Mental Corruption combo, your mana normally isn't a huge factor in that situation. Between nautral regen, and procs from Mental Corruption, your mana normally won't be an issue.  Only time it is normally is if you go crazy with life taps or higher level snares.<br>
